<!DOCTYPE html>
<!-- 
    This HTA file is essential for the UserLogon-MessageBroadcast-GPO.ps1 script to function correctly.
    It provides a graphical interface for user interactions during script execution.
    This HTA is specifically designed to display logon messages broadcasted to users, managed by the corresponding Group Policy Object (GPO).
    Ensure this HTA file is correctly deployed and accessible in the environment where the UserLogon-MessageBroadcast-GPO.ps1 script is implemented,
    to ensure seamless and effective communication with users.
    Author: Luiz Hamilton Silva - @brazilianscriptguy
    Last Updated: 15/01/2024
-->
<html>
<head>
    <title>Logon Message Display</title>
    <hta:application 
        id="logonMessageHTA"
        border="none"
        caption="no"
        contextmenu="no"
        innerborder="no"
        scroll="no"
        showintaskbar="no"
    />
    <style>
        body, html {
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            background-color: #f0f0f0; /* Added background color for better visibility */
        }
        img {
            max-width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            border: 1px solid #ddd; /* Added border for better image visibility */
        }
    </style>
    <script language="VBScript">
        Sub Window_OnLoad
            Dim width, height
            width = 600 ' Specify the width of the window
            height = 800 ' Specify the height of the window
            window.resizeTo width, height
            window.moveTo screen.availWidth\2 - width\2, screen.availHeight\2 - height\2
            idTimer = window.setTimeout("vbscript:window.close", 25000) ' Auto-close after 25 seconds
        End Sub
    </script>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Image showing the logon message. Replace 'post-logon-message.png' with your desired image path -->
    <img src="post-logon-message.png" alt="Logon Message"/>
</body>
</html>
